### ========================================
### ADMIN MODULE A+ FEATURES - POSTMAN TESTS
### ========================================
### Test all 5 critical A+ features for evaluation
### Features: Search/Pagination, Activity Logs, Self-Protection, Rate Limiting, Validation
###
### SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
### 1. Start the server: npm start
### 2. Login as admin to get JWT token
### 3. Replace {{token}} with your actual JWT token
### 4. Replace {{baseUrl}} with http://localhost:5000 (or your server URL)
### 5. Replace {{userId}} with actual user IDs from your database
### ========================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@userId = YOUR_USER_ID_HERE
@adminId = YOUR_ADMIN_ID_HERE

### ========================================
### STEP 1: LOGIN AS ADMIN (Get JWT Token)
### ========================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@university.edu",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Response will contain:
### {
###   "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
###   "user": { ... }
### }
### Copy the token and replace {{token}} above


### ========================================
### FEATURE 1: USER MANAGEMENT WITH VALIDATION
### ========================================

### 1.1 Get All Users (Shows data for search/pagination in frontend)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK with array of users (passwords excluded)


### 1.2 Get Admin Statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK with totalUsers, totalCO2, activeToday, faculties


### ========================================
### FEATURE 2: INPUT VALIDATION (Success & Error Cases)
### ========================================

### 2.1 Update User - VALID REQUEST ✅
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "admin",
  "faculty": "Engineering"
}

### Expected: 200 OK - User updated successfully


### 2.2 Update User - VALIDATION ERROR: Invalid Email ❌
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "invalid-email-format"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request
### {
###   "success": false,
###   "message": "Validation failed",
###   "errors": [
###     {
###       "field": "email",
###       "message": "Please provide a valid email"
###     }
###   ]
### }


### 2.3 Update User - VALIDATION ERROR: Invalid Name (Too Short) ❌
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "A"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - Name must be between 2 and 50 characters


### 2.4 Update User - VALIDATION ERROR: Invalid Name (Special Characters) ❌
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John123!@#"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - Name must contain only letters and spaces


### 2.5 Update User - VALIDATION ERROR: Invalid Role ❌
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "superadmin"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - Role must be either 'user' or 'admin'


### 2.6 Update User - VALIDATION ERROR: No Fields Provided ❌
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - No fields to update. Please provide at least one field.


### 2.7 Update User - VALIDATION ERROR: Invalid User ID Format ❌
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/invalid-id-format
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "admin"
}

### Expected: 400 Bad Request - Invalid user ID format


### ========================================
### FEATURE 3: SELF-PROTECTION RULES
### ========================================

### 3.1 Self-Protection - CANNOT CHANGE OWN ROLE ❌
### Replace {{adminId}} with YOUR logged-in admin's ID
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{adminId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "user"
}

### Expected: 403 Forbidden
### {
###   "success": false,
###   "message": "Cannot modify your own role. Ask another admin for assistance."
### }


### 3.2 Self-Protection - CANNOT DELETE OWN ACCOUNT ❌
### Replace {{adminId}} with YOUR logged-in admin's ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{adminId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 403 Forbidden
### {
###   "success": false,
###   "message": "Cannot delete your own account. This is a security measure to prevent accidental lockout."
### }


### 3.3 Self-Protection - CANNOT DELETE LAST ADMIN ❌
### This test requires only 1 admin in database
### If you have multiple admins, delete all except one first, then try this
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{adminId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 403 Forbidden (if only one admin exists)
### {
###   "success": false,
###   "message": "Cannot delete the last admin. System requires at least one admin."
### }


### 3.4 Delete User - SUCCESS (Non-admin or not self) ✅
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK - User deleted successfully


### ========================================
### FEATURE 4: ACTIVITY LOGS (AUDIT TRAIL)
### ========================================

### 4.1 Get All Activity Logs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/activity-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK
### {
###   "success": true,
###   "logs": [
###     {
###       "_id": "...",
###       "admin": { "name": "...", "email": "..." },
###       "action": "UPDATE",
###       "targetType": "USER",
###       "targetId": "...",
###       "changes": { "before": {...}, "after": {...} },
###       "ipAddress": "::1",
###       "userAgent": "...",
###       "createdAt": "2026-02-27T..."
###     }
###   ],
###   "pagination": {
###     "currentPage": 1,
###     "totalPages": 2,
###     "totalLogs": 15,
###     "logsPerPage": 50
###   },
###   "statistics": {
###     "totalActions": 15,
###     "uniqueAdmins": 2
###   }
### }


### 4.2 Filter Activity Logs by Action (UPDATE)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/activity-logs?action=UPDATE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK - Only logs with action "UPDATE"


### 4.3 Filter Activity Logs by Action (DELETE)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/activity-logs?action=DELETE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK - Only logs with action "DELETE"


### 4.4 Filter Activity Logs by Target Type (USER)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/activity-logs?targetType=USER
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK - Only logs targeting Users


### 4.5 Paginated Activity Logs (Page 1, 10 items)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/activity-logs?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK - 10 logs per page


### 4.6 Filter by Admin ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/activity-logs?adminId={{adminId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK - Logs from specific admin only


### 4.7 Filter by Date Range
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/activity-logs?startDate=2026-02-01&endDate=2026-02-28
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK - Logs within date range


### ========================================
### FEATURE 5: RATE LIMITING
### ========================================

### 5.1 Rate Limiting - General Admin Endpoints (100/15min)
### Run this request 101 times rapidly to trigger rate limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### After 100 requests in 15 minutes:
### Expected: 429 Too Many Requests
### {
###   "success": false,
###   "message": "Too many requests. Please try again in X minutes."
### }
### Headers:
### RateLimit-Limit: 100
### RateLimit-Remaining: 0
### RateLimit-Reset: <unix timestamp>
### Retry-After: <seconds>


### 5.2 Rate Limiting - Strict Operations (20/15min)
### Run this request 21 times rapidly
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "faculty": "Science"
}

### After 20 requests in 15 minutes:
### Expected: 429 Too Many Requests
### {
###   "success": false,
###   "message": "Too many update requests. Please try again in X minutes."
### }


### 5.3 Rate Limiting - Reports (10/15min)
### Run this request 11 times rapidly
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/report
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### After 10 requests in 15 minutes:
### Expected: 429 Too Many Requests
### {
###   "success": false,
###   "message": "Too many report requests. Please try again in X minutes."
### }


### ========================================
### ADDITIONAL TESTS - Authorization & Authentication
### ========================================

### 6.1 Unauthorized Access - No Token ❌
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users

### Expected: 401 Unauthorized
### {
###   "message": "Not authorized, no token"
### }


### 6.2 Unauthorized Access - Invalid Token ❌
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer invalid-token-12345

### Expected: 401 Unauthorized
### {
###   "message": "Not authorized, token failed"
### }


### 6.3 Forbidden - Non-Admin User ❌
### Login as regular user first, then try admin endpoint
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@university.edu",
  "password": "user123"
}

### Then use regular user token:
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer <REGULAR_USER_TOKEN>

### Expected: 403 Forbidden
### {
###   "message": "Access denied. Admin privileges required."
### }


### ========================================
### REPORT ENDPOINTS (Resource Intensive)
### ========================================

### 7.1 Get Report Data (Rate Limited: 10/15min)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/report?startDate=2026-01-01&endDate=2026-02-28
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected: 200 OK with comprehensive report data


### 7.2 Email Report (Rate Limited: 10/15min)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/email-report
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "recipientEmail": "admin@university.edu",
  "startDate": "2026-01-01",
  "endDate": "2026-02-28"
}

### Expected: 200 OK - Report email sent successfully


### 7.3 Get AI Insights (Rate Limited: 10/15min)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/ai-insights
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "data": {
    "totalUsers": 147,
    "totalCO2": 2847.35,
    "topFaculty": "Engineering"
  },
  "question": "What insights can you provide about our sustainability performance?"
}

### Expected: 200 OK with AI-generated insights


